==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lactone
<hw>Lac"tone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>One of a series of organic compounds, being cyclic esters which may
be regarded as anhydrides of certain hydroxy acids. In general, they are
colorless liquids, having a weak aromatic odor. They are so called
because the typical lactone is derived from <xex>lactic</xex>
acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lactonic</ent>⟦br⟧
